CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 10, 1967, pg. 17, reads: "Committee - Among the committee members responsible for the successful AKA "Ajoyo," were this smiling group of sorors. From left Lee Nicklos, basileus, Janet Thompson, Madelyn Hairston, Beverly Johnson, Edythe Perkins, Merlinn Stewart, Delores Gaines, Nan Lewis and Emaline Harper. Miss Johnson is an AKA but was not on the committee."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of eleven women wearing African costumes, including Lee Nicklos, Janet Thompson, Madelyn Hairston, Beverly Johnson, Edythe Perkins, Merlinn (or Merline) Stewart, Delores Gaines, Nan Lewis and Emaline Harper, posed in the Flying Carpet for Alpha Kappa Alpha "Ajoyo"
